The paper discusses the use of Reinforcement Learning and Approximate Dynamic Programming for autonomous decision making in unmanned aircraft systems. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves learning through feedback signals, which is a characteristic of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The problem being addressed involves decision making in a dynamic environment, which can be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves optimizing strategies, which can be categorized under Game Theory (cs.GT).
